<span class="displaytext"><b>for immediate release <br/> contact:</b> (candidate last) press shop (857) 288-6390 <p><b> <u>governor (candidate last)'s tax-free savings plan for nevada families:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will make savings tax free for middle class nevadans.</b> governor (candidate last)'s plan will allow the middle class in nevada to save tax free by changing the tax rate on interest, capital gains and dividends to absolutely 0%. by helping more people in nevada save and invest, we can meet the challenges of an aging population and ensure the financial security of america. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- governor (candidate last)'s plan will allow over 95% of american families to save and invest tax-free.</b> any taxpayer with adjusted gross income of under $200,000 would pay a tax rate of absolutely 0% on all of the income they earn from their savings, capital gains and dividends. </p></blockquote> <p><b>governor (candidate last)'s plan will help hundreds of thousand of nevada taxpayers save and invest tax-free.</b> based on 2005 tax returns: </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- 381,502 nevada taxpayers who earned interest could have benefited from this tax break. <br/> - 172,905 nevada taxpayers who earned dividends could have benefited from this tax break. <br/> - 158,623 nevada taxpayers who earned capital gains could have benefited from this tax break.</b> </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>governor (candidate last)'s plan will help nevadans build wealth and become homeowners:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last)'s plan will help families save for new homes.</b> recent housing market difficulties offer an important reason for helping more people save and invest. as the market softens, credit tightens and lending standards become much tougher. as exotic loans become less widespread, the traditional practice of saving for a home down-payment will be the new standard. governor (candidate last)'s plan will help nevadans save for down-payments and achieve the american dream of home ownership. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- governor (candidate last)'s plan will put more money in the hands of existing homeowners.</b> by providing taxpayers with a 0% tax rate on savings, the plan will help homeowners meet their current mortgage payments. this tax cut will put more money into the hands of nevada homeowners. </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>governor (candidate last)'s plan builds upon and extends pro-growth tax policies:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last)'s plan builds on pro-growth tax policies initiated in 2003.</b> in 2003, the united states passed major cuts in the tax rate on capital gains and dividends, instituting a new, lower top rate of 15%. these tax cuts galvanized our economy. nevadans were able to keep more of their capital gains and reinvest in the economy: </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- the rate of growth in our economy more than tripled, going from 0.8% in the two years before the rate cuts to 3.1% in the two years following the tax cuts. </b></p><p>- following the capital gains tax rate cut in 2003, capital gains tax receipts actually increased from $58 billion in 2002 to $103 billion in 2006. </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>governor (candidate last)'s pro-growth tax agenda:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) has proposed a conservative blueprint to lower taxes and strengthen nevada families.</b> governor (candidate last) will make the bush tax relief permanent, roll back tax rates for all nevadans, abolish the death tax, make health care expenses tax deductible, oppose social security tax increases and make the corporate tax rate more competitive with the rest of the world. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- <a href="http://(candidate full).com/news/press-releases/policy_briefing_blueprint_to_lower_taxes">click here</a> to read governor (candidate last)'s conservative blueprint to lower taxes.</b> </p></blockquote> <p><b>by making the bush tax relief permanent, governor (candidate last) will preserve tax relief for hundreds of thousands of nevada taxpayers:</b> </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- 975,000 nevada taxpayers benefited from the tax relief in 2006. <br/> - 883,000 nevada taxpayers benefited from the rate reduction in the lowest tax bracket in 2006. <br/> - 273,000 nevada couples saw a reduction in the marriage penalty in 2006. <br/> - 239,000 nevada taxpayers benefited from the increased child credit in 2006.</b> </p></blockquote></span>



